rComments: I took this course as a women's study course, and I found she emphasized only one or two issues in women's studies. There were times where she herself said things which completely went against feminist goals. It is hypocritical, and a lot of her work I found to be confusing.

She is a fantastic and smart prof. She makes amazing connections and speaks well. People who say she's a bad prof are just bitter because they didn't understand the material and probably got a bad mark.
her lecture material is prejudice and ****...very hard marker...she expects miracles....unapproachable....material seemed irrelevant to course
What was that?  She has a very awkward way of wording things... Interesting class for sure! but sometimes painful.

Lectures were extremely boring and not at all focused on women as the topic of discussion. The course focused more on race and sexual orientation issues compared to gendered one's. Lectures were not informative as long as you read the articles and watch the films.
I learned a lot in this course. Prof Newman makes the class enjoyable by intermixing video clips with lectures. I would recommend that everyone take this course!
